<section id="research">
  <hr class="section-rule" />
  <p class="label">01 — research</p>
  <h2>What I'm thinking about</h2>
  
  <div class="content">
    <div class="interest">
      <h3>Model Robustness</h3>
      <p>I am interested in how models fail when they encounter distribution shifts and adversarial perturbations. Most benchmarks are too optimistic; I want to understand what it takes to build a model that maintains its reliability when the training assumptions no longer hold.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="interest">
      <h3>Adversarial ML</h3>
      <p>Defenses that work in papers often crumble under real attack surfaces. I study which vulnerabilities actually matter in production and why our current evaluation metrics often fail to capture the true security posture of a system.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="interest">
      <h3>Multimodal Systems</h3>
      <p>Alignment between vision and language is rarely perfect. I explore how different fusion strategies impact the model's ability to reason across modalities, particularly in resource constrained environments where efficiency is as important as accuracy.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="interest">
      <h3>ML in High-Noise Environments</h3>
      <p>Financial data is one of the hardest ML settings that exists — the signal-to-noise ratio is tiny, the distribution shifts constantly, and overfitting is invisible until it costs real money. My work at WorldQuant building and backtesting alpha signals has sharpened how I think about generalization in any domain where clean benchmarks don't exist.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

